<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy — RoomScope" %>
<% content_for :head do %>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for RoomScope, a site survey app for low-voltage, smart home, security, lighting, and custom AV professionals.">
<% end %>

<main class="legal-page">
  <nav class="site-nav legal-nav" aria-label="Main navigation">
    <a class="brand-mark" href="/" aria-label="RoomScope home">
      <span class="brand-icon">RS</span>
      <span>RoomScope</span>
    </a>
    <a class="nav-cta" href="/support">Support</a>
  </nav>

  <article class="legal-card">
    <p class="eyebrow">RoomScope</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: May 31, 2026</p>

    <p>
      RoomScope is a site survey app for low-voltage, smart home, security, lighting, networking,
      and custom AV professionals. This policy explains what information the app handles and how
      to contact us with privacy questions.
    </p>

    <h2>Information you enter in the app</h2>
    <p>
      RoomScope stores site survey projects on your device. This may include project names, room
      names, checklist answers, notes, photos, system categories, and report details that you choose
      to enter while using the app.
    </p>

    <h2>Device storage</h2>
    <p>
      RoomScope is designed around local project capture. Site survey data is stored on your device
      unless you choose to export, share, back up, or otherwise send that information outside the app
      using iOS features such as PDF export or sharing.
    </p>

    <h2>Photos and reports</h2>
    <p>
      If you add photos to a survey or export a PDF report, that content remains part of the project
      data you created. You control who receives exported reports or shared files.
    </p>

    <h2>Purchases</h2>
    <p>
      Solo Pro subscriptions are processed by Apple through the App Store. RoomScope does not receive
      your full payment card details. Apple may provide subscription status information needed to unlock
      paid features in the app.
    </p>

    <h2>Analytics and tracking</h2>
    <p>
      RoomScope does not sell personal information. RoomScope does not use third-party advertising
      trackers in the app.
    </p>

    <h2>Support emails</h2>
    <p>
      If you contact support, we will use the information you provide, such as your email address and
      message, to respond to your request and troubleshoot the issue.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      RoomScope is intended for professional site survey workflows and is not directed to children.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy questions, contact <a href="mailto:support@getroomscope.com">support@getroomscope.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</main>
